@startuml approach1-linq-detailed
title **Approach 1: InMemoryContainer — LINQ Query Flow (Detailed)**

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #333
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #999

actor "Test Code" as Test
participant "InMemoryFeedIteratorSetup" as Setup
participant "InMemoryContainer\n(extends Container)" as IMC
participant "In-memory store\n(ConcurrentDictionary)" as Store
participant "IOrderedQueryable<T>\n(LINQ-to-Objects)" as Queryable
participant "CosmosOverridable\nFeedIteratorExtensions\n(ProductionExtensions pkg)" as Ext
participant "AsyncLocal<Func<>>\nFeedIteratorFactory" as AsyncLocal
participant "InMemoryFeedIterator<T>" as FeedIter
participant "InMemoryFeedResponse<T>\n(extends FeedResponse<T>)" as FeedResp

== One-time Setup (per test fixture) ==

Test -> Setup ++ : InMemoryFeedIteratorSetup.Register()
Setup -> AsyncLocal : Set AsyncLocal<FeedIteratorFactory>\n= CreateInMemoryFeedIterator<T>
Setup --> Test -- : (factory registered)

== Query Building ==

Test -> IMC ++ : GetItemLinqQueryable<T>\n(allowSynchronousQueryExecution,\n continuationToken, requestOptions)
IMC -> Store ++ : GetAllItemsForPartition(requestOptions)
Store --> IMC -- : List<string> (JSON documents)\n(filtered by partition key if set,\n TTL-expired items excluded)
IMC -> IMC : Deserialize each JSON string →\nJsonConvert.DeserializeObject<T>()
IMC -> IMC : Apply requestOptions.PartitionKey\nfiltering if specified
IMC -> Queryable ** : items.AsQueryable()\n.OrderBy(item => 0)\n→ IOrderedQueryable<T>

note right of Queryable
  This is a plain LINQ-to-Objects
  queryable — NOT the Cosmos SDK's
  CosmosLinqQueryProvider. Operators
  execute as C# delegates, not SQL.
end note

IMC --> Test -- : IOrderedQueryable<T>

== LINQ Operator Composition (no execution yet) ==

Test -> Queryable : .Where(x => x.Status == "active")
note right : Adds predicate to expression tree\n(LINQ-to-Objects: C# delegate)
Test -> Queryable : .Select(x => x.Name)
note right : Adds projection to expression tree
Test -> Queryable : .OrderBy(x => x.Timestamp)
note right : Adds sort key to expression tree
Test -> Queryable : .Take(10)
note right : Adds limit to expression tree

== Materialization via ToFeedIteratorOverridable ==

Test -> Ext ++ : .ToFeedIteratorOverridable()

Ext -> AsyncLocal ++ : Check AsyncLocal<FeedIteratorFactory>
AsyncLocal --> Ext -- : factory delegate (non-null,\nset by InMemoryFeedIteratorSetup)

note right of Ext
  Resolution order:
  1. AsyncLocal factory (per-async-flow)
  2. StaticFallbackFactory (static field)
  3. Real SDK .ToFeedIterator() (production)
  In tests, step 1 matches.
end note

Ext -> Setup ++ : factory.Invoke(queryable)\n= CreateInMemoryFeedIterator<T>(queryable)
Setup -> Setup : queryable.AsEnumerable()\n→ triggers LINQ-to-Objects execution:\n  Where → Select → OrderBy → Take\n  all run as C# delegates
Setup -> FeedIter ** : new InMemoryFeedIterator<T>\n(materialized IEnumerable<T>,\n maxItemCount from requestOptions)
Setup --> Ext -- : FeedIterator<T>
Ext --> Test -- : FeedIterator<T>

== Pagination ==

loop while FeedIter.HasMoreResults
  Test -> FeedIter ++ : ReadNextAsync()
  FeedIter -> FeedIter : EnsureItems()\n(materialize enumerable on first call)
  FeedIter -> FeedIter : Paginate: Skip(offset).Take(maxItemCount)
  FeedIter -> FeedIter : Generate continuation token\n(offset-based, null if last page)
  FeedIter -> FeedResp ** : new InMemoryFeedResponse<T>\n(page of items, continuationToken,\n Headers: x-ms-request-charge,\n x-ms-activity-id)
  FeedIter --> Test -- : FeedResponse<T>
end

@enduml
